There is still the following "strange" behavior:

```cpp
// expected to have "noban" and "download" in flags, true
flags = TryParse("noban,download");

// expected to have just "noban" in flags, given that "download" has been removed, not true :(
ClearFlag(flags, PF_DOWNLOAD);

// what happens actually is that now flags is in a "bricked" state
// where it does not equal any of the PF_* flags or a bitwise-OR of them.
```

Could it be avoided to have the download flag included in the noban flag (i.e. to have each PF_* flag have exactly one bit set) and https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/19191 resolved in some other way?

Dropped unneeded parentheses, only change is `git diff d53c70e 7075f60`
```diff
diff --git a/src/net_permissions.h b/src/net_permissions.h
index 9cb59bd85f..7a158aa6c5 100644
--- a/src/net_permissions.h
+++ b/src/net_permissions.h
@@ -56,7 +56,7 @@ public:
     }
     static inline void AddFlag(NetPermissionFlags& flags, NetPermissionFlags f)
     {
-        flags = (flags | f);
+        flags = flags | f;
     }
```

